parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle Module (ETM) can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge without warning, leading to potential accidents, near-crashes, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle stalls in heavy traffic
the vehicle has intermittent electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration Due to Throttle Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle control module can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: and loss of power while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to slow down or stall, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle speed slows down to almost no speed
and loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal arm can cause sudden acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: arm of accelerator pedal breaks when hitting the pad.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: smoke coming out of the tailpipe
engine turning off immediately after starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mount failure can cause the engine to move around in the engine bay, leading to damage to other components, such as radiator hoses, CV axles, and motor mount bushings, which can result in costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine banging around in the engine bay

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle system issues can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: engine turning off immediately after starting

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause warning lights to malfunction, leading to a lack of warning for potential problems, which can increase the risk of accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: ETS light illuminating on the dashboard
wiper blades not working or not aligned properly.
